OL,3,C'I had to tell my Dad he had cancer':
OL,4,CDeaf patients let down by NHS shortages
OL,6,FHis family say he was repeatedly
OL,7,Ffailed by the NHS and indeed when he
OL,8,Fwas diagnosed with an aggressive
OL,9,Fcancer in his eye, it was his daughter
OL,10,Fwho had to break the news to him. He
OL,11,Fhas since died of the disease.
OL,13,FKate Boddy, from Wallasey, says it
OL,14,Ffelt like she stopped being Richard's
OL,15,Fdaughter and became 'the face of the
OL,16,FNHS' as she continued to deliver bad
OL,17,Fnews.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
