OL,3,C'I had to tell my Dad he had cancer':
OL,4,CDeaf patients let down by NHS shortages
OL,6,F"It wasn't just at that moment it was
OL,7,Fright the way through his treatment,
OL,8,Fright up until he died we never knew
OL,9,Fif we were going to get an
OL,10,Finterpreter, an also a lot of the
OL,11,Finformation supplied to him was in
OL,12,Fwritten English, which he couldn't
OL,13,Funderstand.
OL,15,F"So it wasn't just at the physical
OL,16,Fappointments, it was outside of those
OL,17,Fappointments and I became like the
OL,18,Fface of the NHS, the face of the
OL,19,Fhealthcare providers, always telling
OL,20,Fhim the bad news, always telling him
OL,21,Fwhat to do.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
