OL,3,C'I had to tell my Dad he had cancer':
OL,4,CDeaf patients let down by NHS shortages
OL,6,F"He couldn't go online, he couldn't
OL,7,Fjoin support groups and get access to
OL,8,Fthe information most people normally
OL,9,Fdo."
OL,11,FThe British Sign Language act,
OL,12,Fchampioned here in the North West by
OL,13,Fformer Lancashire Labour MP Rosie
OL,14,FCooper whose parents were deaf,
OL,15,Fattempts to tackle that inequality.
OL,17,FBut the RNID says poor training, time
OL,18,Fpressures on staff and even the cost
OL,19,Fis making the NHS a no-go zone for
OL,20,Fthose who can't hear.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
