OL,3,C'I had to tell my Dad he had cancer':
OL,4,CDeaf patients let down by NHS shortages
OL,6,FThe Bolton Deaf Society has been
OL,7,Fhelping people for about 150 years.
OL,8,FMichael Stead is their lead advocate
OL,9,Fand often supports people being
OL,10,Ftreated in the NHS.
OL,12,FMichael said it's no surprise that
OL,13,Fpeople with hearing loss are being let
OL,14,Fdown.
OL,16,FHe says there have been reports in the
OL,17,Fpast and 'absolutely nothing has
OL,18,Fchanged'.
OL,20,FThe NHS has acknowledged concerns
OL,21,Fabout the provision of interpreters.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
